- `Parse(input string)` - Generic parser\n- `ParseForContainer(input)` - Container workflow with location validation\n- `ParseForHost(input)` - Single host workflow\n- `ParseAllForHost(input)` - Multiple workflows in host.cloche\n\n**Parsing features:**\n- Step type inference from `prompt`/`run`/`workflow_name`\n- Workflow-level config blocks (`container {}`, `host {}`)\n- Step-level container blocks (`container { image = \"...\", network_allow = [...] }`)\n- Nested step field parsing with prefix composition (e.g., `container.image`)\n- Output mapping parsing with path expressions\n- Collect parsing with `all`/`any` modes\n- Validation: no orphaned steps, all results wired, location-appropriate step types\n\n### 6. Current Implementation Conventions\n\n**Workflow patterns:**\n1. **Linear workflow** - Sequential steps (hello-world/build.cloche)\n2. **Fanout + collect pattern** - Parallel checks then collect (ruby-calculator, gemini-browser, mini-redis all use this)\n3. **Retry loop** - Failure -> fix step -> retry test (all examples)\n4. **Host orchestration** - Host workflow dispatches container workflows via `workflow_name` steps\n\n**Standard step names observed:**\n- `implement` - Agent step for code generation\n- `test` - Script step for testing\n- `lint` / `clippy` / `rubocop` - Script steps for linting\n- `fmt` / `quality` - Script steps for formatting/quality checks\n- `fix` - Agent step for fixing failures\n- `design` - Agent step for architecture/design (some projects)\n- `prepare-prompt` - Script step for prompt preparation (host workflows)\n- `develop` - Workflow step dispatching container workflow (host workflows)\n\n**Result naming conventions:**\n- `success`, `fail` - Most common\n- `give-up` - When max_attempts exceeded\n- Step-specific results (e.g., `pass`, `retry_with_feedback`)\n\n### 7. Test Fixtures and Integration Examples\n\n**Key test cases in parser_test.go:**\n- `TestParser_FullWorkflow` - Complete workflow with agent and script steps\n- `TestParser_CollectAll` - Parallel fanout with `collect all()` convergence\n- `TestParser_CollectAny` - Race condition with `collect any()`\n- `TestParser_WorkflowNameStep` - Host workflow dispatching container workflow\n- `TestParser_WorkflowNameWithPromptStep` - Workflow step with `prompt_step` parameter\n- `TestParser_InfersTypeFromContent` - Step type inference\n- `TestParser_AmbiguousStepType` - Error on multiple step types\n\n**Example fanout pattern from ruby-calculator/develop.cloche:**\n```\ntest:success -> lint\ntest:success -> quality\nlint:fail -> fix\nquality:fail -> fix\ncollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n```\n\n### 8. Container Setup and Dockerfiles\n\n**Pattern observed:**\n- Most examples use a language-specific base (rust, debian + build tools)\n- All copy `cloche-agent` binary from `cloche-agent:latest` build\n- All install Claude Code via npm: `npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code`\n- Root project Dockerfile extends `cloche-base:latest` and adds language runtimes\n\n**Key conventions:**\n- Non-root `agent` user for security\n- `/workspace` as working directory (project root copied here at runtime)\n- Network isolation by default (`--network none`), allowlist via `network_allow` config\n\n### 9. System Design Document Summary\n\n**Three binaries:**\n- `cloche` - CLI client (run, status, logs, stop)\n- `cloched` - Daemon (container lifecycle, state persistence, gRPC API)\n- `cloche-agent` - In-container autonomous executor (parses DSL, walks graph)\n\n**Hexagonal architecture:**\n- Domain (Workflow, Step, Run types) is infrastructure-agnostic\n- Ports define interfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, AgentAdapter)\n- Adapters implement concrete backends (Docker, SQLite, gRPC)\n\n**Container lifecycle:**\n- One container per workflow run\n- Project files copied to `/workspace/`\n- Results extracted via git branches per run\n- All steps in same container (file state accumulates naturally)\n\n### 10. Latest Conventions Summary\n\n**The current \"latest\" conventions are:**\n\n1. **Fanout + Collect for parallel validation**: Use `collect all()` or `collect any()` rather than sequential checking\n2. **Prompt template pattern**: Store templates in `prompts/` subdirectory and reference via `file(\"prompts/xxx.md\")`\n3. **Script step naming**: Verb-based names like `test`, `lint`, `fmt`, `quality`\n4. **Result naming**: Prefer `success`/`fail` with optional `give-up` for retryable steps\n5. **Max attempts**: Specify `max_attempts = \"N\"` on fix/retry steps\n6. **Host workflow structure**: Three-phase model (list-tasks, main, finalize) for task-driven orchestration\n7. **Agent command configuration**: Specify at workflow-level in `host {}` or `container {}` blocks\n8. **Network security**: Use `network_allow = [...]` lists instead of default open networking\n9. **Output mapping**: Use path expressions like `output.field` or `output[0].name` for inter-step communication\n10. **Step type clarity**: Explicitly declare results for each step, let inference handle type determination\n\nAll file paths are absolute as requested and this represents a comprehensive read-only exploration of the project structure and conventions."}],"totalDurationMs":87038,"totalTokens":55501,"totalToolUseCount":35,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":623,"cache_read_input_tokens":52494,"output_tokens":2378,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":623},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
