[2026-03-13T14:39:21Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DhFPt87DPuRgiTC8gXK4yt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Update Documentation\n     2→\n     3→Compare the current source code against project documentation and update docs to reflect reality.\n     4→\n     5→## Process\n     6→1. Read the source code changes from the current implementation\n     7→2. Grep for specific strings, flags, and config keys in source\n     8→3. Compare against existing documentation\n     9→4. Edit only the sections that are actually out of date\n    10→5. Re-read each file after editing to confirm it is valid\n    11→\n    12→## Rules\n    13→- If no documentation changes are needed, report success immediately\n    14→- Only report fail if an actual write to a doc file failed\n    15→- Do not invent behavior not present in source code\n    16→- If the drift is large, update only sections affected by the current change\n    17→- Spend no more than a few minutes on comparison\n    18→\n    19→## Learned Rules\n    20→- This file was previously corrupted with meta-conversation text (asking for write permissions). Despite the corruption, update-docs succeeded in 26+ consecutive runs. The prompt has been restored to its clean form — if corruption recurs, replace the entire file contents with this canonical version.\n    21→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017KD4BC6dAAhyYJNcBhcasQ","session_id":"38a7cbbe-0157-40c7-bcaa-fa1bfb56d343","uuid":"1d235239-4271-4ddd-b416-06d58e493ac5"}
