[2026-03-13T14:39:21Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017KD4BC6dAAhyYJNcBhcasQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. I've now read all the key reference files. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the complete reference implementation:\n\n## CLOCHE REFERENCE IMPLEMENTATION - COMPLETE CONTENTS\n\n### 1. **Workflow Files**\n\n#### `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` - Container Workflow\nThis defines the coding workflow that runs inside a Docker container:\n- **Step: implement** - Agent step that loads prompt from file, declares success/fail results\n- **Step: test** - Script step that runs `go test ./...` with exit code capture\n- **Step: fix** - Agent step with 2 max attempts, supports success/fail/give-up results\n- **Step: update-docs** - Agent step for documentation updates\n- **Wiring**: implement:success→test, implement:fail→abort, test:success→update-docs, test:fail→fix, fix:success→test (loop), fix:fail→abort, fix:give-up→abort, update-docs:success/fail→done\n\n#### `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` - Host Orchestration Workflow\nRuns on the daemon host machine with three phases:\n- **Config**: `host { agent_command = \"claude\" }`\n- **Step: ready-tasks** - Script that returns available tasks as JSONL\n- **Step: claim-task** - Script that claims a task and transitions it to in_progress\n- **Step: prepare-prompt** - Script that constructs the prompt from task data\n- **Step: develop** - Workflow step that dispatches the develop.cloche container workflow\n- **Step: merge** - Script that rebases feature branch onto main and fast-forwards\n- **Step: cleanup** - Script that removes worktrees and branches\n- **Wiring**: Linear chain with abort on any failure, cleanup:success/fail→done\n\n### 2. **Configuration Files**\n\n#### `/workspace/.cloche/config.toml`\n```toml\nactive = true\n\n[orchestration]\nconcurrency = 3              # Max parallel container workflows\nstagger_seconds = 5.0        # Delay between task dispatches\ndedup_seconds = 300          # Task deduplication window\n\n[evolution]\nenabled = false              # Self-evolution disabled by default\ndebounce_seconds = 30\nmin_confidence = \"medium\"\nmax_prompt_bullets = 50\n```\n\n#### `/workspace/.cloche/Dockerfile`\nMulti-stage from `cloche-base:latest` with:\n- Go 1.25 copied from golang:1.25\n- Node.js and npm installed\n- Claude Code CLI installed globally\n- Runs as non-root `agent` user\n\n### 3. **Prompt Templates**\n\n#### `/workspace/.cloche/prompts/implement.md`\n- Instructs to implement the feature following project conventions\n- Requires writing tests\n- Explicitly requires running `go test ./...` before reporting success\n- Forces fix loop if tests fail\n\n#### `/workspace/.cloche/prompts/fix.md`\n- Directs the agent to fix code based on validation failures\n- Only modifies files that need fixing\n- Requires `go test ./...` after changes\n- Loop until tests pass\n\n#### `/workspace/.cloche/prompts/update-docs.md`\n- Compare source code against documentation\n- Grep for strings, flags, config keys in source\n- Only edit out-of-date sections\n- Reports success if no changes needed\n- Includes learned rule about avoiding meta-conversation corruption\n\n### 4. **Scripts**\n\n#### `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh`\n- Returns unclaimed tasks from `bd` (task database)\n- Accepts optional `max` parameter for limiting results\n- Filters to `open` status only\n- Stores first task's id, title, body in run context via `cloche set`\n- Exits 1 if no tasks available (triggers fail path)\n- Returns JSON array to stdout\n\n#### `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/claim-task.sh`\n- Reads task_id/title/body from run context\n- Runs `bd update \"$CLOCHE_TASK_ID\" --claim`\n- Validates claim succeeded (checks for error in output)\n- Returns task info as properly escaped JSON array\n\n#### `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh`\n- Reads task_title and task_body from run context\n- Constructs prompt as `## Task: {title}\\n\\n{body}`\n- Writes to stdout and to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` if set\n\n#### `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/merge-to-main.sh`\n- Reads child_run_id from run context\n- Creates worktree at feature branch `cloche/{RUN_ID}`\n- Rebases onto main (fails on conflict)\n- Updates branch ref to rebased HEAD\n- Fast-forwards main and deletes feature branch\n- Preserves branch on rebase failure for review\n\n#### `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/cleanup-run.sh`\n- Reads child_run_id and task_id from run context\n- Removes extraction worktree at `.gitworktrees/cloche/{RUN_ID}`\n- Prunes stale worktree bookkeeping\n- Deletes branch if still exists\n- Closes task via `bd close \"$CLOCHE_TASK_ID\"`\n\n### 5. **DSL Documentation and Parser**\n\n#### `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` - Complete DSL Guide\n**Key Concepts**:\n- Workflows define directed graphs of steps connected by named results\n- Steps are inferred: `prompt` field = agent step, `run` field = script step, `workflow_name` field = workflow dispatcher (host-only)\n- Results are named outcomes (e.g., \"success\", \"fail\", \"give-up\")\n- Wiring maps step:result→next-step with optional output mappings\n- `done` and `abort` are built-in terminal steps\n\n**Workflow Locations**:\n- **Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) - Run inside Docker via `cloche-agent`, only allow agent/script steps\n- **Host workflows** (`host.cloche`) - Run on daemon host, allow agent/script/workflow steps, support three phases: list-tasks, main, finalize\n\n**Step Configuration**:\n- `results = [name1, name2, ...]` - Declares possible outcomes\n- `prompt = file(\"path\")` - Agent step with prompt file\n- `run = \"shell command\"` - Script step\n- `workflow_name = \"name\"` - Workflow step (host-only)\n- `max_attempts = \"N\"` - Retry limit for agent steps\n- Sub-blocks for step-level overrides (e.g., `container { image = \"...\" }`)\n\n**Workflow Configuration Blocks**:\n- `container { image, agent_command, agent_args, network_allow }` - Container workflow defaults\n- `host { agent_command, agent_args }` - Host workflow defaults\n\n**Wire Output Mappings**:\n- Syntax: `step:result -> next-step [ KEY = EXPR, ... ]`\n- Path expressions: `output`, `output.field`, `output[N]`, `output.a.b.c`, `output.items[0].name`\n- Resolved values injected as environment variables into target step\n- Validation: no conflicting same-key mappings to same target step\n\n**Collect Statements**:\n- `collect all(step1:result, step2:result) -> next-step` - Wait for all conditions\n- `collect any(step1:result, step2:result) -> next-step` - Wait for any condition\n- Used for fan-in/synchronization in parallel flows\n\n**List-Tasks Schema** (JSONL output):\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"unique-id\",\n  \"status\": \"open|closed|in-progress\",\n  \"title\": \"short summary\",\n  \"description\": \"full description\",\n  \"metadata\": { \"key\": \"value\" }\n}\n```\n\n**Host Workflow Phases**:\n1. `list-tasks` (optional) - Discovers work, output parsed as JSONL\n2. `main` (required) - Executes main workflow, receives `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var\n3. `finalize` (optional) - Post-main cleanup, runs on both success and failure, receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars\n\n#### `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` - Parser Implementation\n**Parser Functions**:\n- `Parse(input string, opts ...ParseOption)` - Parse single workflow with optional location\n- `ParseForHost(input string)` - Parse host workflow (enforces host location)\n- `ParseAllForHost(input string)` - Parse multiple workflows from host.cloche file\n- `ParseForContainer(input string)` - Parse container workflow (rejects workflow_name steps)\n\n**Parsing Details**:\n- Token types: TokenIdent, TokenString, TokenInt, TokenLBrace, TokenRBrace, TokenLBracket, TokenRBracket, TokenColon, TokenArrow, TokenEquals, TokenDot, TokenComma, TokenLParen, TokenRParen, TokenEOF\n- Lexer provides two-token lookahead (current, peek)\n- Step type inference: count of {prompt, run, workflow_name} must be exactly 1\n- Config keys prefixed by block name (e.g., `container.image` from `container { image = ... }`)\n- Workflow-level config stored in `wf.Config`, step-level in `step.Config`\n- Results parsed as ident list `[success, fail, ...]`\n- String lists for some fields: `network_allow = [\"url1\", \"url2\"]`\n- Support for function calls in values: `file(\"path\")`\n- Dotted paths preserved as-is: `step.code.output`\n- Location-based validation: container workflows reject `workflow_name` steps, must have valid location if set\n\n**Output Mappings**:\n- Parsed as bracket-enclosed key=value pairs\n- Path expressions start with `output` keyword\n- Segments can be field names (dot-separated) or indices (bracket-separated)\n- PathSegment union: SegmentField (with Field string) or SegmentIndex (with Index int)\n- Validation: expected \"output\" keyword, proper field names, integer indices\n\n**Collect Statements**:\n- Mode: `all` or `any`\n- Conditions: list of `step:result` pairs in parentheses\n- Arrow `->` to target step\n- Stored in `wf.Collects` slice as `domain.Collect` with Mode, Conditions, To\n\n#### `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go` - Comprehensive Test Fixtures\n**Key Test Scenarios**:\n- Full workflow with multiple steps and complex wiring\n- Minimal workflow (single step)\n- Syntax errors and type mismatches\n- Container/host blocks at workflow level\n- Step-level container blocks\n- Step type inference and ambiguity detection\n- Collect all/any parsing and validation\n- Workflow name steps (host-only)\n- Wire output mappings: single, multiple, array indices, nested access, mixed chaining, bare output\n- Parse errors: missing \"output\" keyword, malformed paths\n- Location enforcement: ParseForHost allows workflow_name, ParseForContainer rejects it\n- ParseAllForHost: multiple workflows, duplicate detection, empty input handling\n- All workflows in ParseAllForHost get LocationHost\n\n### 6. **No Overrides Directory**\nThe glob pattern `/workspace/.cloche/overrides/**` returned no files, indicating this directory is empty or doesn't exist.\n\n---\n\n## SUMMARY OF KEY INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n**Run Context Storage**:\n- `cloche set KEY VALUE` - Store value accessible in later steps\n- `cloche get KEY` - Retrieve stored value\n- `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - Env var pointing to file where step output should be written\n\n**Environment Variables**:\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` - Task ID passed to main workflow\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - Project directory path\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - File path for step output\n- `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` - Outcome of main workflow (in finalize phase)\n- `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` - Run ID of main workflow (in finalize phase)\n\n**External Integrations**:\n- `bd` - Task database CLI (list, update, close operations)\n- `jq` - JSON processing in scripts\n- `go test` - Testing command in test step\n\n**File Paths**:\n- Prompts: `.cloche/prompts/{name}.md`\n- Scripts: `.cloche/scripts/{name}.sh`\n- Worktrees: `.gitworktrees/cloche/{RUN_ID}` and `.gitworktrees/merge/{RUN_ID}`\n- Feature branches: `cloche/{RUN_ID}`\n\n---\n\nAll files have been read in their complete, unmodified form. This is the authoritative reference implementation of Cloche's workflow system."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aef6146c56a5fc40c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 42141\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 47855</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38a7cbbe-0157-40c7-bcaa-fa1bfb56d343","uuid":"d6fb74f6-328c-43a8-b7c5-f9da30f7ecb0","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read ALL files in the root /.cloche/ directory that represent the \"reference\" implementation. I need complete content of:\n\n1. /workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche\n2. /workspace/.cloche/host.cloche\n3. /workspace/.cloche/Dockerfile\n4. /workspace/.cloche/config.toml\n5. All prompt templates in /workspace/.cloche/prompts/\n6. 