[2026-03-13T14:39:21Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017gjrhgbs39rq7peJf1xC51","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issue clearly. The examples have their `.cloche` configuration files (workflow files, Dockerfiles, prompts, scripts) at the project root level, not inside a `.cloche/` subdirectory as the convention dictates.\n\nAccording to CLAUDE.md, the expected structure is:\n```\nmy-project/\n├── .cloche/\n│   ├── develop.cloche      # Container workflow definition\n│   ├── host.cloche          # Host orchestration workflow (runs on host)\n│   ├── Dockerfile           # Container image\n│   ├── prompts/             # Prompt templates for agent steps\n\n\n│   ├── scripts/             # Host-side scripts (e.g. prepare-prompt.sh)\n│   ├── overrides/           # Files copied on top of /workspace/ in container\n│   └── <run-id>/            # Runtime state (gitignored)\n```\n\nBut the examples have these files scattered at the root level instead—the `develop.cloche`, `Dockerfile`, and `prompts/` directory should all be nested inside `.cloche/`, and currently the `.cloche/` directory only contains runtime artifacts like history logs and attempt counts.\n\nSo I need to reorganize by moving the workflow files, Dockerfiles, and prompts into `.cloche/` subdirectories, then update any `file(\"prompts/...\")` references in the workflows since those paths will shift. Let me trace through how the parser resolves these file references to make sure I understand the path resolution correctly.\n\nLooking at the example in `.cloche/develop.cloche`, the `file(\"prompts/implement.md\")` reference resolves relative to the `.cloche/` directory where the workflow file lives, so when I move the prompts into `.cloche/prompts/`, those references should stay the same. I'm also noticing that hello-world keeps its workflow files at the root level with no `.cloche/` directory, while ruby-calculator has a `.cloche/` directory but keeps its workflows and prompts at the root—so there's inconsistency in how these projects are structured. Let me dig into the codebase to see exactly how the file path resolution works.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1233,"cache_read_input_tokens":32388,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1233},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38a7cbbe-0157-40c7-bcaa-fa1bfb56d343","uuid":"0551be98-f2a4-4860-a776-ac89aeb7ad00"}
