[2026-03-13T14:43:44Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PB2FoeV4tsuHgPF56K4Qdh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the information I need. Let me compile my comprehensive findings:\n\n## Workflow DSL Implementation & Conventions - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. **Current DSL Syntax**\n\nThe Cloche workflow DSL is a custom language parsed by `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` using a hand-written lexer (`lexer.go`) and parser. It supports:\n\n**Basic Structure:**\n```\nworkflow \"workflow-name\" {\n  step step-name {\n    [step fields]\n    results = [result1, result2]\n  }\n  \n  [wiring rules]\n  [collect rules]\n}\n```\n\n**Lexer (token.go):** Tokenizes input with support for:\n- Identifiers (with hyphens: `simple-build`)\n- Strings (double-quoted with escape sequences)\n- Operators: `{`, `}`, `[`, `]`, `(`, `)`, `,`, `=`, `->`, `:`, `.`\n- Comments (`//` single-line)\n- Line/column tracking for error reporting\n\n### 2. **Step Types (Inferred from Config)**\n\nThree step types, inferred from which config key is present:\n\n| Type | Config Key | Purpose |\n|------|-----------|---------|\n| **agent** | `prompt` | Invokes a coding agent (Claude, Gemini, etc.) |\n| **script** | `run` | Runs a shell command (`sh -c \"command\"`) |\n| **workflow** | `workflow_name` | Dispatches a container workflow (host workflows only) |\n\n**Validation:** A step must have exactly one of these three keys. Having zero or more than one is a parse error.\n\n### 3. **Available Step Fields**\n\nStored in `Step.Config` map as `key: value` strings.\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Notes |\n|-------|------|----------|-------|\n| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | if agent | Template text or file reference |\n| `run` | string | if script | Shell command executed via `sh -c` |\n| `workflow_name` | string | if workflow | Name of container workflow to dispatch |\n| `results` | list of idents | yes | Possible outcomes: `[success, fail]`, `[success, fail, give-up]`, etc. |\n| `max_attempts` | string | no | Max retries (e.g., `\"3\"`); generates `give-up` result when exceeded |\n| `timeout` | string | no | Go duration format (e.g., `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`) |\n| `agent_command` | string | no | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains (e.g., `\"claude,gemini\"`) |\n| `agent_args` | string | no | Override default agent arguments as space-separated flags |\n| `feedback` | string | no | Set to `\"true\"` to inject `.cloche/output/*.log` content into prompt |\n| `prompt_step` | string | no | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt |\n| `container.*` | string | no | Container-level config (see below) |\n| `host.*` | string | no | Host-level config (see below) |\n\n**Known Keys Validation:** The parser validates against `knownStepConfigKeys` in `workflow.go:246`. Any unknown keys generate warnings during validation, useful for catching typos.\n\n### 4. **Current .cloche File Formats**\n\n**Project Layout** (migrated in commit `0c9112f`, March 2, 2026):\n```\nmy-project/\n├── .cloche/                          # All Cloche-specific files\n│   ├── develop.cloche                # Container workflow(s)\n│   ├── host.cloche                   # Host workflow(s) - optional\n│   ├── Dockerfile                    # Container image\n│   ├── prompts/                      # Prompt template files\n│   │   ├── implement.md\n│   │   ├── fix.md\n│   │   └── ...\n│   ├── scripts/                      # Host-side scripts\n│   │   ├── prepare-prompt.sh\n│   │   ├── ready-tasks.sh\n│   │   └── ...\n│   ├── overrides/                    # Container-specific file overrides\n│   └── evolution/                    # Evolution snapshots (auto-generated)\n├── src/                              # Project source (left untouched)\n└── CLAUDE.md\n```\n\n**Workflow Files:**\n- Container workflows: `develop.cloche`, `build.cloche`, etc. (any `.cloche` file except `host.cloche`)\n- Host workflows: only `host.cloche`\n\n**File Locations:** The parser supports multiple functions to parse different contexts:\n- `Parse(input, opts...)` - generic with optional location\n- `ParseForContainer(input)` - enforces `LocationContainer`\n- `ParseForHost(input)` - single workflow\n- `ParseAllForHost(input)` - multiple workflows in one file\n\n### 5. **Workflow-Level Configuration Blocks**\n\nTwo block types (not mixed in the same workflow):\n\n**`container {}` block** - Container workflows:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    image = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n    agent_args = \"-p --dangerously-skip-permissions\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\nSupported keys: `image`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `network_allow`.\nStored in `Workflow.Config` with `container.` prefix.\n\n**`host {}` block** - Host workflows only:\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n    agent_args = \"-p\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\nSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\nStored in `Workflow.Config` with `host.` prefix.\n\n**Resolution Order (agent_command):**\n1. Step-level `agent_command`\n2. Workflow-level block `agent_command`\n3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` env var\n4. Default: `\"claude\"`\n\n### 6. **Wiring Syntax**\n\nTwo wiring mechanisms:\n\n**Simple Wiring:**\n```\nstep:result -> next_step\n```\nExample:\n```\nimplement:success -> test\nimplement:fail -> abort\ntest:success -> done\ntest:fail -> fix\nfix:success -> test  // loops back\nfix:fail -> abort\nfix:give-up -> abort\n```\n\n**Collect Wiring** (converging branches, added in commit `77589e4`):\n```\ncollect all(step1:result1, step2:result2) -> target\ncollect any(step3:result3, step4:result4) -> target\n```\n- `collect all(...)` — proceed when ALL conditions are met\n- `collect any(...)` — proceed when ANY condition is met\nExample (ruby-calculator):\n```\ncollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n```\n\n**Output Mappings** (extract JSON and inject as env vars):\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output[0].name ]\n```\nPath expressions:\n- `output` - raw output string\n- `output.field` - JSON object field\n- `output[N]` - JSON array index\n- `output.a.b.c` - nested field access\n- `output.items[0].name` - mixed navigation\n\nValidation: No duplicate env var names targeting the same step (would be ambiguous).\n\n### 7. **File References**\n\nThe `file(\"path\")` function:\n```\nprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n```\n- Reads relative to `/workspace/` in containers\n- Evaluated at **execution time**, not parse time\n- Used for prompt templates, not dynamic content\n\nThe parser captures this as a literal string (including the function call syntax) in `Step.Config`. The prompt adapter later reads the file.\n\n### 8. **Container & Host Workflows**\n\n**Container Workflows:**\n- Run inside Docker containers via `cloche-agent`\n- Located in `.cloche/*.cloche` (anything except `host.cloche`)\n- Only support `agent` and `script` step types\n- Use `container {}` block for config\n- Parse with `ParseForContainer()`\n\n**Host Workflows:**\n- Run on the host machine via the daemon\n- Only in `.cloche/host.cloche`\n- Support `agent`, `script`, AND `workflow` step types\n- Use `host {}` block for config\n- Parse with `ParseAllForHost()` for multiple workflows\n- Three-phase orchestration:\n  1. `list-tasks` - discover work (optional, JSONL output)\n  2. `main` - process task (required)\n  3. `finalize` - cleanup (optional, runs on success/failure)\n- Enforcement: `workflow_name` steps in container workflows are parse errors\n\n### 9. **Recent Changes to DSL/Config**\n\n**Commit `64c6827` (Mar 6, 2026):** Feedback injection opt-in\n- Added `feedback = \"true\"` config key to conditionally include `.cloche/output/*.log` in prompts\n- Previously feedback was injected unconditionally, causing \"prompt too long\" failures\n- Known key: `feedback` added to `knownStepConfigKeys`\n\n**Commit `0c9112f` (Mar 2, 2026):** Layout migration from `cloche/` to `.cloche/`\n- Projects no longer need to restructure files\n- Full project root copied to container at `/workspace/`\n- `.cloche/overrides/` mechanism for container-specific overrides\n- Updated all path references across CLI, daemon, evolution\n\n**Commit `530bd29` (Feb 24, 2026):** DSL Mutator and TOML config\n- `AddStep(input, StepDef)` - insert step into workflow text\n- `AddWiring(input, []WireDef)` - append wires\n- `RewireResult(input, from, result, oldTo, newTo)` - change wire target\n- `UpdateCollect(input, CollectAddition)` - add condition to collect clause\n- All operations validate result by re-parsing\n\n**Commit `77589e4` (Feb 25, 2026):** Collect wiring syntax\n- `collect all(...)` and `collect any(...)` for converging branches\n- Stored in `Workflow.Collects` slice\n- Conditions validate that step exists and result is declared\n\n**Commit `d6c3086` (Mar 6, 2026):** Enforce host.cloche convention\n- `workflow_name` steps only allowed in host workflows\n- Container workflows validated to reject `StepTypeWorkflow`\n\n### 10. **Domain Types** (from `internal/domain/workflow.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n  Name    string\n  Type    StepType\n  Results []string\n  Config  map[string]string\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n  From      string\n  Result    string\n  To        string\n  OutputMap []OutputMapping\n}\n\ntype OutputPath struct {\n  Segments []PathSegment\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n  Name      string\n  Location  WorkflowLocation  // \"container\" or \"host\"\n  Steps     map[string]*Step\n  Wiring    []Wire\n  Collects  []Collect\n  EntryStep string\n  Config    map[string]string\n}\n\ntype Collect struct {\n  Mode       CollectMode  // \"all\" or \"any\"\n  Conditions []WireCondition\n  To         string\n}\n```\n\n**Validation Methods:**\n- `Validate()` - checks entry step exists, all results wired, no orphans, no duplicate output mappings\n- `ValidateLocation()` - enforces `workflow_name` only in host workflows\n- `ValidateConfig()` - warns about unknown config keys\n\n### 11. **Conventions for .cloche Directory**\n\n**Dockerfiles:**\n- Located at `.cloche/Dockerfile`\n- Must install build tools and agent (e.g., Claude CLI)\n- Example from mini-redis uses standard base images\n- Network policies applied at runtime via daemon\n\n**Prompt Files:**\n- Located in `.cloche/prompts/` (e.g., `implement.md`, `fix.md`)\n- Referenced via `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`\n- Placeholder: `(Contents of .cloche/prompt.txt will be injected here by the adapter)`\n- User request injected at runtime via `.cloche/prompt.txt` (from daemon)\n\n**Script Files:**\n- Located in `.cloche/scripts/` (e.g., `prepare-prompt.sh`, `ready-tasks.sh`)\n- Host scripts execute from main branch worktree (even if on different branch)\n- Can access `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`\n- Output written to `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` for downstream steps\n\n**Override Files:**\n- Located in `.cloche/overrides/`\n- Copied on top of `/workspace/` in container (useful for container-specific config)\n- Example: `CLAUDE.md` override with different settings for in-container agent\n\n**.gitignore Convention:**\n```\n.cloche/*/                # Runtime dirs per run\n!.cloche/prompts/         # Check in prompts\n!.cloche/overrides/       # Check in overrides\n!.cloche/evolution/       # Check in evolution snapshots\n.gitworktrees/            # Temporary worktrees\n```\n\n### 12. **DSL Parser Implementation Details**\n\n**Lexer (`lexer.go`):**\n- Supports identifiers with hyphens (for step/result names)\n- String literals with escape sequences (`\\\"`, `\\\\`, `\\n`, `\\t`)\n- Tracks line/column for error reporting\n- Comments via `//`\n\n**Parser (`parser.go`):**\n- Two-token lookahead (`current`, `peek`)\n- Infers step type at parse time from config keys\n- Supports nested config blocks (`container { ... }`, `host { ... }`)\n- Results parsed as ident lists: `results = [success, fail]`\n- Config values can be:\n  - String literals: `run = \"make test\"`\n  - Identifiers/dotted paths: `agent_command = claude`\n  - Function calls: `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`\n  - Ident lists (for results): `[success, fail, give-up]`\n  - String lists: `network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\"]`\n\n**Validation:**\n- Graphs validated at parse time\n- All declared results must have wiring\n- All steps except entry must be reachable\n- Wire conditions validated (step/result existence)\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe Cloche DSL is a **declarative, graph-based workflow language** designed for autonomous coding agents. Key design principles:\n\n1. **Type inference** — step type from config keys (prompt/run/workflow_name)\n2. **Result-driven routing** — steps declare results; wiring defines graph\n3. **Separation of concerns** — step definitions separate from wiring (enables evolution)\n4. **Location-aware** — host workflows support workflow dispatch; container workflows are self-contained\n5. **Validation at parse time** — catches errors early\n6. **Container model** — full project copied in; overrides for container-specific files\n7. **Additive evolution** — Mutator for safe workflow modifications\n\nThe implementation is mature, with recent enhancements for feedback control, layout flexibility, and workflow composition."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a734ac1dadeea8114 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 69039\ntool_uses: 42\nduration_ms: 111438</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"87510e8f-028e-4687-9903-d33073502bb8","uuid":"33affd3c-6c76-463e-a89b-e63138e79727","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the current workflow DSL implementation and conventions. I need to understand:\n\n1. What is the current DSL syntax? Read the workflow parser/lexer code and docs/workflows.md\n2. What step types are supported? (agent, script, etc.)\n3. What fields are available on steps?\n4. What is the current format for .cloche files (develop.cloche, host.cloche)?\n5. What conventions exist for Dockerfiles, prompts, scripts, and overrides?\n6. Are there any recent changes to the DSL or config format?\n\nFocus on:\n- internal/domain/ for types\n- Any parser/lexer code for the DSL\n- docs/workflows.md\n- The .cloche directory structure conventions\n- cmd/ for any CLI flags or config\n\nRead the key files thoroughly and report back all findings about the current state of the implementation.","agentId":"a734ac1dadeea8114","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the information I need. Let me compile my comprehensive findings:\n\n## Workflow DSL Implementation & Conventions - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. **Current DSL Syntax**\n\nThe Cloche workflow DSL is a custom language parsed by `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` using a hand-written lexer (`lexer.go`) and parser. It supports:\n\n**Basic Structure:**\n```\nworkflow \"workflow-name\" {\n  step step-name {\n    [step fields]\n    results = [result1, result2]\n  }\n  \n  [wiring rules]\n  [collect rules]\n}\n```\n\n**Lexer (token.go):** Tokenizes input with support for:\n- Identifiers (with hyphens: `simple-build`)\n- Strings (double-quoted with escape sequences)\n- Operators: `{`, `}`, `[`, `]`, `(`, `)`, `,`, `=`, `->`, `:`, `.`\n- Comments (`//` single-line)\n- Line/column tracking for error reporting\n\n### 2. **Step Types (Inferred from Config)**\n\nThree step types, inferred from which config key is present:\n\n| Type | Config Key | Purpose |\n|------|-----------|---------|\n| **agent** | `prompt` | Invokes a coding agent (Claude, Gemini, etc.) |\n| **script** | `run` | Runs a shell command (`sh -c \"command\"`) |\n| **workflow** | `workflow_name` | Dispatches a container workflow (host workflows only) |\n\n**Validation:** A step must have exactly one of these three keys. Having zero or more than one is a parse error.\n\n### 3. **Available Step Fields**\n\nStored in `Step.Config` map as `key: value` strings.\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Notes |\n|-------|------|----------|-------|\n| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | if agent | Template text or file reference |\n| `run` | string | if script | Shell command executed via `sh -c` |\n| `workflow_name` | string | if workflow | Name of container workflow to dispatch |\n| `results` | list of idents | yes | Possible outcomes: `[success, fail]`, `[success, fail, give-up]`, etc. |\n| `max_attempts` | string | no | Max retries (e.g., `\"3\"`); generates `give-up` result when exceeded |\n| `timeout` | string | no | Go duration format (e.g., `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`) |\n| `agent_command` | string | no | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains (e.g., `\"claude,gemini\"`) |\n| `agent_args` | string | no | Override default agent arguments as space-separated flags |\n| `feedback` | string | no | Set to `\"true\"` to inject `.cloche/output/*.log` content into prompt |\n| `prompt_step` | string | no | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt |\n| `container.*` | string | no | Container-level config (see below) |\n| `host.*` | string | no | Host-level config (see below) |\n\n**Known Keys Validation:** The parser validates against `knownStepConfigKeys` in `workflow.go:246`. Any unknown keys generate warnings during validation, useful for catching typos.\n\n### 4. **Current .cloche File Formats**\n\n**Project Layout** (migrated in commit `0c9112f`, March 2, 2026):\n```\nmy-project/\n├── .cloche/                          # All Cloche-specific files\n│   ├── develop.cloche                # Container workflow(s)\n│   ├── host.cloche                   # Host workflow(s) - optional\n│   ├── Dockerfile                    # Container image\n│   ├── prompts/                      # Prompt template files\n│   │   ├── implement.md\n│   │   ├── fix.md\n│   │   └── ...\n│   ├── scripts/                      # Host-side scripts\n│   │   ├── prepare-prompt.sh\n│   │   ├── ready-tasks.sh\n│   │   └── ...\n│   ├── overrides/                    # Container-specific file overrides\n│   └── evolution/                    # Evolution snapshots (auto-generated)\n├── src/                              # Project source (left untouched)\n└── CLAUDE.md\n```\n\n**Workflow Files:**\n- Container workflows: `develop.cloche`, `build.cloche`, etc. (any `.cloche` file except `host.cloche`)\n- Host workflows: only `host.cloche`\n\n**File Locations:** The parser supports multiple functions to parse different contexts:\n- `Parse(input, opts...)` - generic with optional location\n- `ParseForContainer(input)` - enforces `LocationContainer`\n- `ParseForHost(input)` - single workflow\n- `ParseAllForHost(input)` - multiple workflows in one file\n\n### 5. **Workflow-Level Configuration Blocks**\n\nTwo block types (not mixed in the same workflow):\n\n**`container {}` block** - Container workflows:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    image = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n    agent_args = \"-p --dangerously-skip-permissions\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\nSupported keys: `image`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `network_allow`.\nStored in `Workflow.Config` with `container.` prefix.\n\n**`host {}` block** - Host workflows only:\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n    agent_args = \"-p\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\nSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\nStored in `Workflow.Config` with `host.` prefix.\n\n**Resolution Order (agent_command):**\n1. Step-level `agent_command`\n2. Workflow-level block `agent_command`\n3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` env var\n4. Default: `\"claude\"`\n\n### 6. **Wiring Syntax**\n\nTwo wiring mechanisms:\n\n**Simple Wiring:**\n```\nstep:result -> next_step\n```\nExample:\n```\nimplement:success -> test\nimplement:fail -> abort\ntest:success -> done\ntest:fail -> fix\nfix:success -> test  // loops back\nfix:fail -> abort\nfix:give-up -> abort\n```\n\n**Collect Wiring** (converging branches, added in commit `77589e4`):\n```\ncollect all(step1:result1, step2:result2) -> target\ncollect any(step3:result3, step4:result4) -> target\n```\n- `collect all(...)` — proceed when ALL conditions are met\n- `collect any(...)` — proceed when ANY condition is met\nExample (ruby-calculator):\n```\ncollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n```\n\n**Output Mappings** (extract JSON and inject as env vars):\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output[0].name ]\n```\nPath expressions:\n- `output` - raw output string\n- `output.field` - JSON object field\n- `output[N]` - JSON array index\n- `output.a.b.c` - nested field access\n- `output.items[0].name` - mixed navigation\n\nValidation: No duplicate env var names targeting the same step (would be ambiguous).\n\n### 7. **File References**\n\nThe `file(\"path\")` function:\n```\nprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n```\n- Reads relative to `/workspace/` in containers\n- Evaluated at **execution time**, not parse time\n- Used for prompt templates, not dynamic content\n\nThe parser captures this as a literal string (including the function call syntax) in `Step.Config`. The prompt adapter later reads the file.\n\n### 8. **Container & Host Workflows**\n\n**Container Workflows:**\n- Run inside Docker containers via `cloche-agent`\n- Located in `.cloche/*.cloche` (anything except `host.cloche`)\n- Only support `agent` and `script` step types\n- Use `container {}` block for config\n- Parse with `ParseForContainer()`\n\n**Host Workflows:**\n- Run on the host machine via the daemon\n- Only in `.cloche/host.cloche`\n- Support `agent`, `script`, AND `workflow` step types\n- Use `host {}` block for config\n- Parse with `ParseAllForHost()` for multiple workflows\n- Three-phase orchestration:\n  1. `list-tasks` - discover work (optional, JSONL output)\n  2. `main` - process task (required)\n  3. `finalize` - cleanup (optional, runs on success/failure)\n- Enforcement: `workflow_name` steps in container workflows are parse errors\n\n### 9. **Recent Changes to DSL/Config**\n\n**Commit `64c6827` (Mar 6, 2026):** Feedback injection opt-in\n- Added `feedback = \"true\"` config key to conditionally include `.cloche/output/*.log` in prompts\n- Previously feedback was injected unconditionally, causing \"prompt too long\" failures\n- Known key: `feedback` added to `knownStepConfigKeys`\n\n**Commit `0c9112f` (Mar 2, 2026):** Layout migration from `cloche/` to `.cloche/`\n- Projects no longer need to restructure files\n- Full project root copied to container at `/workspace/`\n- `.cloche/overrides/` mechanism for container-specific overrides\n- Updated all path references across CLI, daemon, evolution\n\n**Commit `530bd29` (Feb 24, 2026):** DSL Mutator and TOML config\n- `AddStep(input, StepDef)` - insert step into workflow text\n- `AddWiring(input, []WireDef)` - append wires\n- `RewireResult(input, from, result, oldTo, newTo)` - change wire target\n- `UpdateCollect(input, CollectAddition)` - add condition to collect clause\n- All operations validate result by re-parsing\n\n**Commit `77589e4` (Feb 25, 2026):** Collect wiring syntax\n- `collect all(...)` and `collect any(...)` for converging branches\n- Stored in `Workflow.Collects` slice\n- Conditions validate that step exists and result is declared\n\n**Commit `d6c3086` (Mar 6, 2026):** Enforce host.cloche convention\n- `workflow_name` steps only allowed in host workflows\n- Container workflows validated to reject `StepTypeWorkflow`\n\n### 10. **Domain Types** (from `internal/domain/workflow.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n  Name    string\n  Type    StepType\n  Results []string\n  Config  map[string]string\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n  From      string\n  Result    string\n  To        string\n  OutputMap []OutputMapping\n}\n\ntype OutputPath struct {\n  Segments []PathSegment\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n  Name      string\n  Location  WorkflowLocation  // \"container\" or \"host\"\n  Steps     map[string]*Step\n  Wiring    []Wire\n  Collects  []Collect\n  EntryStep string\n  Config    map[string]string\n}\n\ntype Collect struct {\n  Mode       CollectMode  // \"all\" or \"any\"\n  Conditions []WireCondition\n  To         string\n}\n```\n\n**Validation Methods:**\n- `Validate()` - checks entry step exists, all results wired, no orphans, no duplicate output mappings\n- `ValidateLocation()` - enforces `workflow_name` only in host workflows\n- `ValidateConfig()` - warns about unknown config keys\n\n### 11. **Conventions for .cloche Directory**\n\n**Dockerfiles:**\n- Located at `.cloche/Dockerfile`\n- Must install build tools and agent (e.g., Claude CLI)\n- Example from mini-redis uses standard base images\n- Network policies applied at runtime via daemon\n\n**Prompt Files:**\n- Located in `.cloche/prompts/` (e.g., `implement.md`, `fix.md`)\n- Referenced via `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`\n- Placeholder: `(Contents of .cloche/prompt.txt will be injected here by the adapter)`\n- User request injected at runtime via `.cloche/prompt.txt` (from daemon)\n\n**Script Files:**\n- Located in `.cloche/scripts/` (e.g., `prepare-prompt.sh`, `ready-tasks.sh`)\n- Host scripts execute from main branch worktree (even if on different branch)\n- Can access `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`\n- Output written to `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` for downstream steps\n\n**Override Files:**\n- Located in `.cloche/overrides/`\n- Copied on top of `/workspace/` in container (useful for container-specific config)\n- Example: `CLAUDE.md` override with different settings for in-container agent\n\n**.gitignore Convention:**\n```\n.cloche/*/                # Runtime dirs per run\n!.cloche/prompts/         # Check in prompts\n!.cloche/overrides/       # Check in overrides\n!.cloche/evolution/       # Check in evolution snapshots\n.gitworktrees/            # Temporary worktrees\n```\n\n### 12. **DSL Parser Implementation Details**\n\n**Lexer (`lexer.go`):**\n- Supports identifiers with hyphens (for step/result names)\n- String literals with escape sequences (`\\\"`, `\\\\`, `\\n`, `\\t`)\n- Tracks line/column for error reporting\n- Comments via `//`\n\n**Parser (`parser.go`):**\n- Two-token lookahead (`current`, `peek`)\n- Infers step type at parse time from config keys\n- Supports nested config blocks (`container { ... }`, `host { ... }`)\n- Results parsed as ident lists: `results = [success, fail]`\n- Config values can be:\n  - String literals: `run = \"make test\"`\n  - Identifiers/dotted paths: `agent_command = claude`\n  - Function calls: `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`\n  - Ident lists (for results): `[success, fail, give-up]`\n  - String lists: `network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\"]`\n\n**Validation:**\n- Graphs validated at parse time\n- All declared results must have wiring\n- All steps except entry must be reachable\n- Wire conditions validated (step/result existence)\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe Cloche DSL is a **declarative, graph-based workflow language** designed for autonomous coding agents. Key design principles:\n\n1. **Type inference** — step type from config keys (prompt/run/workflow_name)\n2. **Result-driven routing** — steps declare results; wiring defines graph\n3. **Separation of concerns** — step definitions separate from wiring (enables evolution)\n4. **Location-aware** — host workflows support workflow dispatch; container workflows are self-contained\n5. **Validation at parse time** — catches errors early\n6. **Container model** — full project copied in; overrides for container-specific files\n7. **Additive evolution** — Mutator for safe workflow modifications\n\nThe implementation is mature, with recent enhancements for feedback control, layout flexibility, and workflow composition."}],"totalDurationMs":111438,